FR940610-0-00132 FR940610-0-00023 (ii) If a donor transferred an interest in property by gift after December 31, 1988, and before May 1, 1989, retaining an interest in the same property, and after April 30, 1989, and before January 1, 1990, transferred the retained interest in property, the donor may, at the option of the donor, value the transfer of the retained interest under this section or under §25.2512&hyph;5A(d). (4) Publications and actuarial computations by the Internal Revenue Service. Many standard actuarial factors not included in §20.2031&hyph;7(d)(6) of this chapter are included in Internal Revenue Service Publication 1457, ``Actuarial Values, Alpha Volume,'' (8&hyph;89). Internal Revenue Service Publication 1457 also includes examples that illustrate how to compute many special factors for more unusual situations. A copy of this publication may be purchased from the Superintendent of Documents, United States Government Printing Office, Washington, DC 20402. If a special factor is required in the case of a completed gift, the Service may furnish the factor to the donor upon a request for a ruling. The request for a ruling must be accompanied by a recitation of the facts including a statement of the date of birth for each measuring life, the date of the gift, any other applicable dates, and a copy of the will, trust, or other relevant documents. A request for a ruling must comply with the instructions for requesting a ruling published periodically in the Internal Revenue Bulletin (see §§601.201 and 601.601(d)(2)(ii)( b ) of this chapter) and include payment of the required user fee. (e) Effective date. This section is effective as of May 1, 1989. §25.2512&hyph;9 [Removed] Par. 31. Section 25.2512&hyph;9 is removed. Par. 32. Section 25.2515&hyph;2, paragraph (c) is amended by revising the first and last sentences to read as follows: §25.2515&hyph;2 Tenancies by the entirety; transfers treated as gifts; manner of election and valuation. * * * * * (c) Fact